3. AQAROON_NODE_FLEET.md (paste)AQAROON Node FleetAn AQAROON is a cheap, self‑contained AQARIONZ node: one device + sensors + local storage, owned by a person or family, not a platform.Minimal AQAROONHardware: old Android phone / Raspberry Pi‑class board.Sensors: microphone, IMU, optional HR/EEG strap.Software: AQARIONZ core backend, local database, optional sync to GitHub.RolesHome node, cave‑node, river‑node, “storm porch” node.Each writes Signal and SessionLog entries using the same schemas (so data can be compared later).TODOExact minimal spec for each node type.Simple install scripts / checklists
